::Tiered Response::In the tiered response approach, what is the purpose of the "holding statement" issued within 5-15 minutes?{
~To provide complete details about the crisis and resolution plan #Complete details come in medium-term response (24-48 hours), not holding statement. The point of holding statement is you DON'T have complete info yet.
=To acknowledge the situation and commit to providing updates #Lecture Slide 12 explained tiered response\: "Immediate (5-15 min)\: Holding statement - 'We're aware and investigating.'" Purpose is to ACKNOWLEDGE the situation and COMMIT to providing updates, not to provide complete details (that comes in later tiers).
~To assign blame and take full responsibility for the crisis #Assigning blame and taking full responsibility is not appropriate for a holding statement issued within 15 minutes - you haven't investigated yet.
~To announce the crisis has been resolved #Announcing resolution happens only after crisis is actually resolved, which is not within 15 minutes.
}

