::Social Media Crisis Management::Which of the following is considered a crisis communication BEST PRACTICE for social media management?{
~Delete negative comments to control the narrative #Slide 18 explicitly said "Don't delete negative comments (shows you're hiding)." Deletion creates screenshot evidence and proves guilt.
~Wait until you have complete information before responding on social media #This violates speed principle - you should issue holding statement within 15 minutes, not wait for complete information.
=Respond publicly AND privately (DMs for individual concerns) #Slide 18 (Social Media Crisis Management) listed best practices, including\: "Respond publicly AND privately (DMs for individual concerns)." This balances transparency (public response) with personalized support (private DMs).
~Limit social media updates to once per day to avoid overwhelming followers #During crisis, more frequent updates are better (every 1-3 hours in active crisis phase), not once per day.
}

